title: Issue completing the download due to "Uncaught Type Error"??
body: I recently had to factory reset my laptop due to memory issues, and when I went to re download LoL the entire download went fine until the end when it would apply the updates and complete the download. It gives me an "Uncaught TypeError" It says to check the log for more info and then there is the retry button. I retried and got the same message, does anyone know what could cause this issue and how to correct it?

replies.body: Well I've gotten the game to fully download, but I've met yet another issue. I went to load into a match and then couldnt due to what the games "bug splat" said was a corrupt file. Now every time I try to repair the file the scan makes it to about 4% and then stop and makes no further progress.
I've never heard of this error before. Can you take a screenshot and post it to [Imgur](https://imgur.com/) or [Gyazo](https://gyazo.com/), then post the link here so I can take a look? Thanks!

Thanks for getting back to me with that screenshot. Running into issues at 33% during the patching process usually happens when the client is unable to establish a stable connection to the patching servers in order to pull new files for the patch. There are certainly a lot of factors that could cause an unstable connection, but our [connection troubleshooting guide](https://support.riotgames.com/hc/en-us/articles/201752664-Troubleshooting-Connection-Issues) will walk you through the most common solutions.

If you still have issues patching after working through that connection guide, please let me know.
